-- Oil Rises as Bernanke Call for Looser Policy Spurs Demand Hopes
-- B y   G r a n t   S m i t h
-- 2012-03-26T12:10:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-26/oil-rises-as-bernanke-call-for-looser-policy-spurs-demand-hopes.html
Oil rose, recovering earlier
losses, after Federal Reserve Chairman  Ben S. Bernanke  said
accommodative policy is needed to lower unemployment, causing a
drop in the dollar that made commodities more attractive.
Futures gained as much as 0.2 percent to $107.09 a barrel on the
 New York Mercantile Exchange .  To contact the reporter on this story:
